# Sprint 9.7.0 Item 1 (foundation) — Gradle wrapper force-include.
# Mirrors the e2ee-app main-branch pattern. The default
# `flutter create --platforms=android` template excludes
# `gradlew`, `gradlew.bat`, and `gradle-wrapper.jar` because
# they are "generated by gradle wrapper". For a CLEAN refactor
# that produces a buildable artifact on a fresh clone, we
# commit them (per the CI workflow comment: "For this workflow
# to successfully ./gradlew assembleDebug in CI, mobile/android/
# gradlew must exist on the runner — either committed via the
# standard Flutter scaffold OR regenerated before the build step
# via `flutter create . --platforms=android`"). We choose
# "committed via the standard Flutter scaffold" because:
#   1. It is one-time work per branch, not per CI run.
#   2. It is reproducible: every fresh `git clone` has the wrapper.
#   3. The android-debug.yml workflow's "Make gradlew executable"
#      step + "Build Debug APK" step both fail with
#      "No such file or directory" without these three files.
!gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar
!/gradlew
!/gradlew.bat

# Remember to never publicly share your keystore.
# See https://flutter.dev/to/reference-keystore
key.properties
**/*.keystore
**/*.jks
